social_posts.post_text: Double whirlwind x 12 @405. Who tryna kendama/ lift battle. I might be only moderately good at both of these things but who out there is better at both 😂

Finally 315 bebehhhh
Happy Valentine’s Day to the luckiest girl in the world. I don’t know how I ever did it without @bbyrankin . I never knew it could be this good. Love you honey.
Thank you for all the love and birthday wishes everyone. Turned 35 yesterday and I’m excited for this next chapter of life. Gratitude almost feels like an understatement.

Sunday officially marked my final performance with @magicmikelive. There’s simply no words to describe this chapter of my life. Whatever you think it was, it was 10x crazier I promise. 

Life long friendships, love, lust, ballin, broke, resentment, amends and everything in between. In the end the feeling of gratitude is what overwhelms me the most today. The life and opportunities that have been built here are immeasurable. The bond I have with some of the people in this chapter was forged in the fire of creation, love, art, and most of all FUN. I’ll probably never have a job again where I’m supported to be the class clown and make sure that web of fun and creative spirit holds everything together (sorry @alison_faulk for sometimes pushing the limit on this while you try to do your job 😂). Not to mention I met the woman of my dreams on my drum kit @bbyrankin 🥹

There comes a point in a lot of journeys where it becomes easy, or comfortable. At some point it is time to ask what it is serving in your life. Your gut will tell you but you might not be ready to listen. Is it serving growth or comfort. Don’t ignore your gut. 

I don’t know that I have ever experienced a happy cry like I did this night. Thank you everyone that was a part of it near and far. I don’t know that I will be able to catch up on all the messages wishing me well on the next chapter of life.
Finally making some time to get out on this thing. 🤤🤤🤤 the @ebcbrakes rotors and @stealthpipes exhaust are easily sone of the hardest parts on this build.

How many fads and hacks will we see before people just start doing the basics. Eat (good), sleep, exercise. Timing exactly when you drink your coffee and getting sun on your butthole will do next to nothing compared to taking the time out of your life for the basics. 
Side note- coffee does not dehydrate you. Look at the data. 

485 for 6. Just wanted it on the grid.

Stop listening to what people on instagram say (I say from my instagram profile). You body can do crazy things. Prepare it for whatever you want. You can strengthen your spinal flexion safely and “functional fitness” is the stupidest term ever. Thank you for reading my rant.
